abstract: United Nations' official expresses alarm over unusual expulsion of his group and other humanitarian agencies from eastern Ukraine by Russian-backed separatists; claims order to leave amounts to violation of international law; UN figures show conflict between rebels and government forces has killed almost 8,000 people and displaced 1.4 million.
lead_paragraph: It is rare that United Nations agencies are ordered to cease operations in a country or region.

headline.main: U.N. Agencies Told to Leave East Ukraine
headline.print_headline: U.N. Agencies Told to Leave East Ukraine
